erscommittees executive profile jeff kearl founder and vice president of business development freeportcom incagetotal calculated compensationthis person is connected to  board members in  different organizations across  different industriessee board relationships background mr jeff kearl serves as the chief executive officer and chairman of stance mr kearl cofounded precedent investments in  he serves as a venture partner of zetta venture partners mr kearl served as chief strategy officer and chief marketing officer of arteis inc from april  to april  mr kearl served as director of strategy and new ventures for hewlett packard he ran strategy and new ventures at hp mr kearl served as the chief marketing officer  of logoworks he also overseen new internal business units within logoworks such as diy design and was responsible for corporate development including venture capital financing and ma and cofounded the firm mr kearl worked as an associate at vspring capital he served as an associate at vspring iii lp vspring i lp and vspring ii lp prior to vspring capital he founded freeportcom inc and served as its vice president of business development  product marketing he was also involved with several startups such as cerberian comscore control mediconnect global and senforce in  mr kearl cofounded and served as vice president of sales of apex training  development previously he spent four years in management consulting focused on organizational development and competitive strategy mr kearl started his career at the covey leadership center where he worked in various sales marketing and product management roles until it was acquired by franklin quest in  he serves as the chairman of stance mr kearl serves as a director of needle inc julep stance and connect sdsi he serves as a member of advisory boards of several utah companies he served as the director of skullcandy inc from  to october   and chairman until june   mr kearl teaches entrepreneurial finance in the marriott 